t month is one of gradual, if choppy, upside progression. From the 160.50\u2013160.60 area \u2014 a prior reaction zone that has now registered four distinct touches and absorbed selling pressure on multiple occasions \u2014 the pair has built a series of higher lows across the daily timeframe. The 30 June surge through 162.00 was the defining moment, establishing fresh near-term highs above 162.84 before a corrective flush back toward 160.60 on 2 July briefly tested conviction. That the zone held cleanly, with buyers re-engaging and price subsequently reclaiming 162.00 with relative ease by 6 July, speaks to the underlying demand structure. The cluster of closes between 162.19 and 162.64 across the past week suggests the market is digesting those gains rather than distributing them.\n\nOn the hourly chart, the intraday read is one of orderly consolidation following a measured overnight bid. Price climbed from around 162.10 during the late London session on Wednesday, extended through 162.45 in the early Asian hours, and has since settled into a tight range between roughly 162.35 and 162.45. Hourly candles are printing small bodies with contained wicks \u2014 a pattern consistent with a market pausing rather than reversing. The 162.30 area, where the overnight advance found its footing, represents the nearest intraday structure reference worth watching.\n\nToday's economic calendar carries no scheduled high-impact events for either the US or Japan, which removes a significant source of exogenous volatility from the equation. In the absence of data catalysts, price action is likely to remain technically driven, with the pair susceptible to moves generated by broader risk sentiment shifts or any commentary from Federal Reserve or Bank of Japan officials that crosses the wires informally.\n\nThe scenario that would challenge the current bullish read is a decisive daily close back below the 161.50 area, which has acted as a pivot on several occasions during the consolidation phase. A more meaningful structural shift would only come into view on a sustained break beneath the 160.60 prior reaction zone \u2014 the level that has repeatedly absorbed downside pressure and would need to give way convincingly before the broader trend narrative came into question.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}